channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Report: Kamala Harris Will Hold First Rally With Running Mate Next Week After Announcement
Delaware Republican running for governor aims to flip one-party rule in Biden's home state after three decades
item.description: Mike Ramone, running to become Delaware's first GOP governor in 32 years, said he plans to beat one-party rule in President Biden's home state.

item.title: Kari Lake Wins GOP Primary For Arizona Senate Race
item.description: Kari Lake won the Republican nomination for U.S. Senate in Arizona on Tuesday, setting up a fierce fight against Democrat Rep. Ruben Gallego for a seat that could be crucial to deciding Senate control.

item.title: Florida Man Arrested After Making Unhinged Remarks About Trump Assassination Attempt and JD Vance's Kids
Gillibrand, Hawley lead bipartisan bill to create mental health hotline for police, first responders
item.description: Sens. Gillibrand and Hawley team up to introduce a bill to establish a grant program to help provide mental health resources and a support hotline for first responders.

item.title: Rep. Waltz to Newsmax: Trump Shooter May Have Had Help
item.description: Rep. Michael Waltz, R-Fla., told Newsmax his concerns about the possibility that the shooter who attempted to assassinate former President Donald Trump may have had assistance.

item.title: The Irrational Exuberance Among Democrats About Harris
Watchdog group launching 'Hate Map' to track 'political violence perpetrated by leftist organizations'
item.description: The New Tolerance Campaign is launching an interactive map to catalog groups promoting or engaging in political violence across the United States.

item.title: Sen. Murkowski Hits Vance Over 'Childless Cat Ladies' Quip
item.description: Sen. Lisa Murkowski, R-Alaska, is criticizing the Republican vice presidential nominee, Sen. J.D. Vance, R-Ohio, saying his comments criticizing "childless cat ladies" were offensive.

item.title: BREAKING: Kari Lake Wins GOP Senate Primary, Will Face Gallego in General Election
Emhoff hobnobs on Nantucket while fishermen reel from wind turbine 'disaster'
item.description: A New England fishermen's association is calling attention to second gentleman Doug Emhoff's fundraising trip to Nantucket as fishermen deal with the aftermath of a wind turbine disaster.

item.title: Bill O'Reilly to Newsmax: Too Soon to Clean House at Secret Service
item.description: Author Bill O'Reilly told Newsmax on Tuesday a thorough investigation into the operational breakdowns resulting in the attempted assassination of former President Donald Trump should be conducted before any disciplinary action is taken at the Secret Service.

item.title: BREAKING: Senior Hamas Leader Ismail Haniyeh Assassinated on Iranian Soil
Republican wins primary for Ruben Gallego's House seat but remains long shot in November
item.description: Voters in Arizona's 3rd Congressional District are now going to decide whether a Democrat or Republican should replace Rep. Ruben Gallego.

item.title: Harris to Be Sole Dem Presidential Candidate Heading Into Party Vote
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris is the only White House hopeful who has qualified to compete for the Democratic presidential nomination, the Democratic National Committee said in a statement on Tuesday. Although no other major Democrat had indicated any plans to challenge ...
